ation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Omega Labyrinth Z]]''\n|Banned because of interactive sexual activity involving a person who is, or appears to be, a minor.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Postal (video game)]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Postal 2]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Postal III]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Predator: Concrete Jungle]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Quake 4]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence. A censored version was released.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Red Ninja: End of Honor]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence. A censored version was released.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Reservoir Dogs (video game)|Reservoir Dogs]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Resident Evil 4]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact violence related to incentives and rewards via two unlockable bonus games. A censored version was released. The ban was lifted in 2017.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Resident Evil: Operation Raccoon City]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence. A censored version was released.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Resident Evil: The Umbrella Chronicles]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Return to Castle Wolfenstein]]''\n|Originally given a 16+ rating with Nazi references censored. Later banned for high-impact gory violence.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n|''[[Saints Row]]''\n|Banned because of high-impact gory violence. A censored version was released.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n|-\n